In [[Māori mythology]], '''Rangahore''' is a wife of god [[Tāne]]. Tāne was looking for a wife, and asked his mother [[Rangi and Papa|Papa]] to suggest suitable candidates. He took Rangahore to wife, but she gave birth to a stone, and Tane forsook her (Shortland 1882:20-21, Tregear 1891:391).<ref>E. Shortland, ''Maori Religion and Mythology'' ([[Longmans]]: London), 1882.</ref><ref>[[E. R. Tregear]], ''Maori-Polynesian Comparative Dictionary'' ([[Lyon and Blair]]: Lambton Quay), 1891.
</ref>

