{{Multiple issues|{{Refimprove|date=June 2015}}{{Cleanup-reorganize|date=June 2015}}}}
A '''stevna''' (plural: '''stevnur''') is a regional summer festival in the [[Faroe Islands]], usually accompanied by or built around national rowing boat championships.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.visitfaroeislands.com/en/what-to-do/what%C2%B4s-on-2015-highlights/|title=What´s on: 2015 Highlights|work=Visit Faroe Islands}}</ref> The races and regattas are always held on Saturdays, except the [[Ólavsøka]] race in the capital of [[Tórshavn]], which has a fixed date. There are seven official rowing-related''stevnur'':<ref>{{cite web|url=http://rsf.fo/stevnur/ |title=Stevnur &#124; Rsf |publisher=Rsf.fo |date= |accessdate=2015-06-25}}</ref>
== Stevnur in the Faroe Islands == *[[Norðoyastevna]] is held annually in [[Klaksvík]], usually in the first weekend of June.<ref name="Visitnordoy">{{cite web|url=http://www.visitnordoy.fo/UK/index.asp?pID={016C6314-D13B-4396-9D44-39F803F912A9}|title=Nordoyastevna - in Klaksvik|publisher=Visitnordoy.fo|accessdate=8 July 2015}}</ref> *[[Eystanstevna]] is held in [[Runavík]] the second weekend of June every year, and has a rowing race every other year. In the odd years (2005, 2007 etc.) the race is held at the Varmakelda.<ref name="Visiteysturoy">{{cite web|url=http://www.visiteysturoy.fo/uk/index.asp?pID={3161CFC7-37EA-4FA2-A0EA-1CFF28FD28D9}|title=Eystanstevnan|publisher=Visiteysturoy.fo|accessdate=8 July 2015}}</ref> *[[Sundalagsstevna]] is held in a weekend in mid-June in the Sundalagið region. The host town alternates between [[Kollafjørður]], [[Hósvík]] and [[Hvalvík]]. *[[Jóansøka]] is in the last weekend of June, or the Saturday nearest to the 24th of June, which is [[St John’s Day]]. In the even years it is held in [[Vágur]] and in the odd years in [[Tvøroyri]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.visitsuduroy.fo/UK/index.asp?pID={9564A453-480A-475B-A1A1-DE96BFC5D4E1} |title=Suðuroy - EN - Events - Jóansøka |publisher=Visitsuduroy.fo |date=2010-06-21 |accessdate=2015-07-09}}</ref> *[[Varmakelda]] is usually the first weekend in July in [[Fuglafjørður]]. A rowing race is held every odd year; in the other years it is held in Runavík.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.visiteysturoy.fo/uk/index.asp?pID={F74DA030-B785-4E4A-8555-E6E8BDCB350E} |title=Eysturoy - EN - Events - Village Festivals - Varmakeldustevna |publisher=Visiteysturoy.fo |date= |accessdate=2015-07-09}}</ref> *[[Vestanstevna]] is usually a weekend in the first half of July, and shifts between the three towns of [[Sandavágur]], [[Miðvágur]] and [[Sørvágur]]. *[[Fjarðastevna]] is celebrated in a weekend somewhere mid-July. In the even years it is held in [[Vestmanna]], whereas in the odd years the host town alternates between [[Strendur]] and [[Skáli]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.visiteysturoy.fo/uk/index.asp?pID={A0E6E9CE-E1D3-44DF-A94C-979EED72F519} |title=Eysturoy - EN - Events - Village Festivals - Fjarðastevna |publisher=Visiteysturoy.fo |date= |accessdate=2015-07-09}}</ref> *[[Ólavsøka]] is the national holiday of the Faroe Islands with many festivities of all kinds in the capital of [[Tórshavn]], including the opening of Parliament. Whereas the other ''stevnur'' tend to be more-less regional festivals, this ''stevna'' is a national event. It is held at the 29th of July, whilst the rowing championships are held the wake before, on 28 July.
Other '''stevnur'''', that do not include rowing regattas, are held in various places, such as the Útoyggjastevna<ref>{{cite web|url=http://utoyggj.fo/pages/utoyggjastevnan.php |title=utoyggj.fo |publisher=Utoyggj.fo |date= |accessdate=2015-06-25}}</ref> for all the outpost islands, the Sandoyarstevna on Sandoy,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sandportal.fo/her-er-skrain-fyri-sandoyarstevnuna/|title=Sandportal » Blog Archive » Her er skráin fyri Sandoyarstevnuna|work=sandportal.fo}}</ref> and boating festivals for modern boats in various places.
